The epic document has been written to `/home/stephan/src/FairEmail/docs/epics/14.6-system-mailto-handler.md`. It covers:

- Registration as the system's `mailto:` handler
- RFC 6068 URI parsing (To, CC, BCC, Subject, Body)
- Compose window pre-population and cold-start behavior
- Account/identity selection logic (primary account fallback, smart matching)
- Error handling for no-account and malformed-URI scenarios
- Sanitization of invisible characters and HTML injection prevention
- Send-to-self convenience shortcut
- Open questions around non-standard extensions (`aid`, `in-reply-to`), XDG registration strategy, and body format ambiguity
